{"description":"Coffee is one of the most underrated devs in the space. A builder who talks less and ships more, but when he does speak up, you’d be smart to listen.

In a timeline full of noise, CoffeeX delivers signal  whether he’s sharing insights on token mechanics, smart contract architecture, or the future of onchain culture. His posts don’t chase engagement; they earn it. Quietly consistent, deeply technical, and refreshingly grounded.

You won’t catch him farming clout or flexing vaporware. You will catch him building, observing the meta shift in real-time, and occasionally dropping a thread or take that’ll stick with you long after the scroll.

If you’re looking to follow devs who actually get it and don’t need hype to prove it @coffeexcoin should be at the top of your list."}

translation.translatedDescription:
Coffee is one of the most underrated devs in the space. A builder who talks less and ships more, but when he does speak up, you’d be smart to listen.

In a timeline full of noise, CoffeeX delivers signal  whether he’s sharing insights on token mechanics, smart contract architecture, or the future of onchain culture. His posts don’t chase engagement; they earn it. Quietly consistent, deeply technical, and refreshingly grounded.

You won’t catch him farming clout or flexing vaporware. You will catch him building, observing the meta shift in real-time, and occasionally dropping a thread or take that’ll stick with you long after the scroll.

If you’re looking to follow devs who actually get it and don’t need hype to prove it @coffeexcoin should be at the top of your list.

data.metadata: {"description":"DeBuddha is one of those rare voices in the timeline who brings both consistency and clarity. He doesn’t chase hype or flood feeds with noise instead, he adds value with every post. Whether it’s a sharp insight, a grounded take, or a quiet nod to a project worth watching, his presence is intentional and measured. You can tell he’s here for the long game, focused on building and learning rather than grabbing attention. It’s a refreshing energy in a space that often leans chaotic.\n\nWhat really stands out is his reliability and community-first mindset. DeBuddha shows up, not just when things are loud, but especially when it matters—supporting others, contributing to the conversation, and bringing balance to the room. He’s the type of person you want in your digital corner: engaged, humble, and quietly influential. There’s strength in that kind of steady participation, and DeBuddha exemplifies it."}

translation.translatedDescription:
DeBuddha is one of those rare voices in the timeline who brings both consistency and clarity. He doesn’t chase hype or flood feeds with noise instead, he adds value with every post. Whether it’s a sharp insight, a grounded take, or a quiet nod to a project worth watching, his presence is intentional and measured. You can tell he’s here for the long game, focused on building and learning rather than grabbing attention. It’s a refreshing energy in a space that often leans chaotic.

What really stands out is his reliability and community-first mindset. DeBuddha shows up, not just when things are loud, but especially when it matters—supporting others, contributing to the conversation, and bringing balance to the room. He’s the type of person you want in your digital corner: engaged, humble, and quietly influential. There’s strength in that kind of steady participation, and DeBuddha exemplifies it.
